  "root_text": {
    "sn4.15:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 4.15 ",
    "sn4.15:0.2": "2. Dutiyavagga ",
    "sn4.15:0.3": "Mānasasutta ",
    "sn4.15:1.1": "Evaṁ me sutaṁ—",
    "sn4.15:1.2": "ekaṁ samayaṁ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṁ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ",
    "sn4.15:1.3": "Atha kho māro pāpimā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṁ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ",
    "sn4.15:2.1": "“Antalikkhacaro pāso, ",
    "sn4.15:2.2": "yvāyaṁ carati mānaso; ",
    "sn4.15:2.3": "Tena taṁ bādhayissāmi, ",
    "sn4.15:2.4": "na me samaṇa mokkhasī”ti. ",
    "sn4.15:3.1": "“Rūpā saddā rasā gandhā, ",
    "sn4.15:3.2": "Phoṭṭhabbā ca manoramā; ",
    "sn4.15:3.3": "Ettha me vigato chando, ",
    "sn4.15:3.4": "Nihato tvamasi antakā”ti. ",
    "sn4.15:4.1": "Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṁ bhagavā, jānāti maṁ sugato”ti dukkhī dummano tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn4.15:0.1": "Linked Discourses 4.15 ",
    "sn4.15:0.2": "2. Rule ",
    "sn4.15:0.3": "A Mental Snare ",
    "sn4.15:1.1": "So I have heard. ",
    "sn4.15:1.2": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. ",
    "sn4.15:1.3": "Then Māra the Wicked went up to the Buddha and addressed him in verse: ",
    "sn4.15:2.1": "“There’s a mental snare ",
    "sn4.15:2.2": "wandering in midair. ",
    "sn4.15:2.3": "I’ll bind you with it—",
    "sn4.15:2.4": "you won’t escape me, ascetic!” ",
    "sn4.15:3.1": "“Sights, sounds, tastes, smells, ",
    "sn4.15:3.2": "and touches so delightful: ",
    "sn4.15:3.3": "desire for these is gone from me. ",
    "sn4.15:3.4": "You’re beaten, terminator!” ",
    "sn4.15:4.1": "Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The Buddha knows me! The Holy One knows me!” miserable and sad, vanished right there. "
  },
